tmjos-dock (1.3.0-2) noble; urgency=medium

  * tmjos-first-run now explicitly enables tmjos-tweaks@tmjos.local
    via `gnome-extensions enable`. Reason: gnome-shell writes [] to
    user-db on first launch, overriding the system-db default set by
    tmjos-defaults. Per-user enable in first-run wins and persists.
    Observed on v1.3.0-2 install: Activities button visible despite
    correct dconf system override.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 12:20:00 -0300

tmjos-dock (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial .deb release.
  * Replaces phase 6f/6g/6h/6h.5 of v1.2 customize.sh.
  * Plank is pre-configured with 4 sticky launchers; the All Apps
    launcher is re-injected by tmjos-first-run if removed.
  * tmjos-dock-sync daemon mirrors GNOME favorite-apps into Plank
    so pinning via the Activities Overview shows up in the dock.
  * tmjos-show-apps now uses Super+A (single-tap to apps grid) with
    toggle behavior via a state file.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 19:00:00 -0300
